the fair value of long-term debt is estimated using discounted cash flow analyses, based on the
companys incremental borrowing rates for similar types of borrowing arrangements. the fair value of the companys long-term debt, including current portion, is approximately $674.0 million at may31, 2006 and $721.2 million at
